    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        WINDSHIELD GLASS - WINDSHIELD REMOVE (Figure 22 )
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>WINDSHIELD REMOVE (
            <hotlnk document="s16006_19.xml" xrefid="f1600622">Figure 22</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <para>If either the windshield glass or the weatherseals are to be replaced, the following procedures should be
            used.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Use a secure work platform, high enough to enable a person outside the front of the vehicle to
                    comfortably and safely perform the windshield glass and weatherseal removal and installation.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the windshield washer hose from fitting. Lift spring loaded latch to unlock wiper arm
                and lift wiper arm off shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600623">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600623" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600623" filename="../figg16/g1600623.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Exploded View of Wiper Arm Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WASHER HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FITTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOCK LATCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. WIPER ARM</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. WIPER BLADE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully pry locking strip (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600624">Figure 24</hotlnk>) from the perimeter weatherseal.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600624" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600624" filename="../figg16/g1600624.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Removing Weatherseal Locking Strip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SEAL TOOL KM-J2189-02</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCKING STRIP (STANDARD OR CHROME)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WEATHERSEAL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully pry the center locking strip (Item 1,
                <hotlnk document="s16006_19.xml" xrefid="f1600622">Figure 22</hotlnk>) from weatherseal center section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Separate the windshield halves from the perimeter seal and remove the windshield glass from
                the opening.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the weatherseal is damaged, it must be replaced.
                <emph type="bold">Do not remove the weatherseal if it is not damaged.</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Any deformation or irregularities on the seal mounting fence which could cause improper
                        seating of the weatherseal must be repaired.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
